==English==
===Etymology===
Italian ''corridore'' (=''[[corridoio]]'') "long passage" < ''[[correre]]'' "to run"

===Pronunciation===
/ˈkɒrəˌdoː/

===Noun===
'''corridor'''
# A [[narrow]] [[hall]] or [[passage]] with [[room]]s leading off.
# A [[restrict]]ed [[tract]] of [[land]] that allows passage between two places.
# [[Airspace]] restricted for the passage of [[aircraft]].

====Related terms====
* [[corridors of power]]
*[[w:Polish corridor|Polish corridor]]

